cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB

The paper discusses data citation practices and the use of a database to link data sets and data studies with citations received from other citation indexes. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and databases (cs.DB). However, given the focus on data citation practices and the use of a citation index, we believe that cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CY, cs.CR, and cs.DB.
